@node "Config"

INSTALLATION CHANGES

All configuration files starting with OctaMEDPro should be renamed to start
with Soundstudio. In other words, OctaMEDPro.config, OctaMEDPro.defkeyboard
and OctaMEDPro.defprogkeys should be renamed Soundstudio.config,
Soundstudio.defkeyboard and Soundstudio.defprogkeys.

This change can be made through OctaMED, when you run the Soundstudio for the
first time:

  Load your old files, all starting with OctaMEDPro, one by one in the usual
  way. That is, use the Settings menu for .config, the Keyboard Shortcuts
  window for .defkeyboard and the Programmable Keys window for .defkeys.

  Save the files under their new names. To do this, select Save Settings
  from the Settings menu, Save in the Keyboard Shortcuts window (remembering
  to rename the file to Soundstudio.defkeyboard), and Save Keys in the
  Programmable Keys window (again, rename the file).

  Select Delete Files from the Project menu and delete the old .config files.


